  "dcterms:description": "First-run Holo Spaces. Members reference real app root κs (the same roots gen-apps-catalog stamps into holospaces.jsonld). A 'space' member references another seed by id; the app resolves it to that Space's computed κ at load — so nesting carries no hardcoded κ and stays re-derivable. The home is a 'honeycomb' lobby: a Space-of-Spaces shown as a pannable hex wall. One of its hexes ('discover') is itself a honeycomb, proving infinite nesting. 'author' is presentation (the hover label) and does NOT enter a Space's κ identity (identity = the arrangement, not who posted it).",
